headline: Advanced Micro Devices’ Winning Streak Continues. How High Can the Chip Stock Go?
summary: AMD shares are up 25% over that eight-day period and have soared more than 100% over the past year.  The iShares Semiconductor exchange-traded fund is up 51% over the past 12 months, bolstered in recent weeks by Intel’s sudden surge.  Intel is getting love for its new processors and positive comments from President Donald Trump, while AMD has, in comparison, flown under the radar to start 2026.

headline: AI race: How export restrictions may be giving US an advantage
summary: Anthropic (ANTH.PVT) CEO Dario Amodei likened permitting the sales of AI chips to China to "selling nuclear weapons to North Korea." Council on Foreign Relations (CFR) senior fellow for China and emerging technologies, Chris McGuire, reacts to these comments and how the US leads China in hardware development amid a tightening AI race. Also catch Chris McGuire's comments on the quality of China's AI progress compared to the US. headline: AMD price target raised to $225 from $200 at Bernstein
summary: Bernstein analyst Stacy Rasgon raised the firm’s price target on AMD (AMD) to $225 from $200 and keeps a Market Perform rating on the shares ahead of quarterly results. The firm is adjusting estimates to incorporate better server / weaker PC assumptions.
